Notes
	•	Column F (trigger condition) is encoded under conditions.rules (using the ops we already support: eq|ne|changed|changedTo|becameNotNull|becameNull).
	•	Column G (trigger timing) drives the new "schedule" object:
	•	immediate → enqueue now.
	•	atField → enqueue at the date in that field (+ optional time, tz).
	•	afterDaysFromField → enqueue days after a date field.
	•	cron → for monthly “around 10th”. If that’s truly a global batch day, a Timer trigger is the cleanest place; but I included cron here to keep it all in one config if you want Service Bus scheduled deliveries.

